DEFAULT_ASYNCHRONOUS_WRITE

static final boolean DEFAULT_ASYNCHRONOUS_WRITE
True if you want to write file asynchronously. You can define the number of thread dedicate to write file in FactoryCsvWriter. By default the number of processor divide by 3. If you create several files in the same time, the thread will be share for each files.

Since:
0.0.1

DEFAULT_FIELD_POSITION

static final int DEFAULT_FIELD_POSITION

Position of field in file. The first position of the first field is 1. It is not required that position numbers follow. The default position is -1.

If no position is required you can set a negative position. If you want to override a CsvField annotation in sub class, you must set a negative value other than -1

Since:
0.0.1
See Also:

DEFAULT_FIELD_NAME
